      <header class="mb-12">
        <div class="text-sm text-primary font-medium mb-4">June 21, 2025</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-playfair text-darktext mb-6">Lash Extension Styles Explained</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-mediumtext">Understanding different lash styles helps you choose the perfect look. Comprehensive guide from Orange County lash professionals.</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Choosing the right lash extension style can transform your entire look. Understanding different styles, mapping techniques, and curl types helps you communicate your vision to your Orange County lash artist and achieve the perfect result for your eye shape and personal style.</p>

        <h2>Popular Lash Extension Styles</h2>

        <h3>Natural Style</h3>
        <p>Subtle enhancement that looks like your lashes, only better:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> 9-11mm, staying close to natural lash length</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Classic or light volume application</li>
          <li><strong>Curl:</strong> C or CC curl for natural lift</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> First-time clients, professional environments, everyday wear</li>
          <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Lower maintenance, subtle shedding less noticeable</li>
          <li><strong>Orange County lifestyle:</strong> Perfect for active, beachy lifestyle</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Cat Eye Style</h3>
        <p>Longer lashes at outer corners create elegant, elongated appearance:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> Gradually increasing from 9mm inner to 13-14mm outer</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Works with any volume level</li>
          <li><strong>Curl:</strong> C or D curl for definition</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Hooded eyes, almond shapes, evening looks</li>
          <li><strong>Effect:</strong> Elongates eye shape, creates sultry appearance</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal occasions:</strong> Date nights, Newport Beach galas</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Doll Eye Style</h3>
        <p>Longer lashes in center create open, wide-eyed look:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> Longest in center (12-13mm), shorter at corners</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Medium to dramatic volume</li>
          <li><strong>Curl:</strong> D or DD curl for maximum lift</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Close-set eyes, round eyes, cute aesthetic</li>
          <li><strong>Effect:</strong> Opens up eyes, creates innocent, youthful look</li>
          <li><strong>Popular with:</strong> Younger clients, special events</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Wispy Style</h3>
        <p>Textured, feathery appearance with varying lengths:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> Mixed lengths creating spike effect (10-14mm)</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Volume or hybrid techniques</li>
          <li><strong>Curl:</strong> C or D curl for dimension</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Modern, trendy look, all eye shapes</li>
          <li><strong>Effect:</strong> Dimension and texture, Instagram-worthy</li>
          <li><strong>Trending in:</strong> Orange County social scene</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Dramatic Style</h3>
        <p>Maximum length, volume, and impact:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> 13-16mm throughout lash line</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Heavy volume (4D-6D or mega volume)</li>
          <li><strong>Curl:</strong> D or DD curl for dramatic effect</li>
          <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Special occasions, performers, bold personalities</li>
          <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Higher maintenance required</li>
          <li><strong>Orange County events:</strong> Weddings, galas, photo shoots</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Understanding Curl Types</h2>

        <h3>J Curl</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Most natural, subtle lift</li>
          <li>Best for clients with already lifted lashes</li>
          <li>Creates understated enhancement</li>
          <li>Less common, suitable for specific eye shapes</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>B Curl</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Slight curl, natural appearance</li>
          <li>Good for straight natural lashes</li>
          <li>Professional, subtle look</li>
          <li>Comfortable for first-time clients</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>C Curl</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Most popular curl type</li>
          <li>Natural curl with visible lift</li>
          <li>Versatile for most eye shapes</li>
          <li>Opens eyes without looking dramatic</li>
          <li>Perfect for Orange County everyday wear</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>CC Curl</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Between C and D curl intensity</li>
          <li>More lifted than C, less dramatic than D</li>
          <li>Great for slightly hooded eyes</li>
          <li>Popular choice for balanced look</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>D Curl</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Dramatic, glamorous lift</li>
          <li>Opens hooded or deep-set eyes</li>
          <li>Creates doll-eye effect</li>
          <li>Popular for special occasions</li>
          <li>More maintenance required</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>DD or U Curl</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Most dramatic curl available</li>
          <li>Maximum lift and impact</li>
          <li>Best for very hooded eyes</li>
          <li>Special events and photo shoots</li>
          <li>Requires strong natural lashes</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>L Curl</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Flat base with lifted tip</li>
          <li>Specifically for hooded or monolid eyes</li>
          <li>Creates lift where others can't</li>
          <li>Growing in popularity</li>
          <li>Excellent retention on difficult eye shapes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Choosing Based on Eye Shape</h2>

        <h3>Almond Eyes</h3>
        <p>Most versatile eye shape, suits all styles:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> Any style works beautifully</li>
          <li><strong>Popular choices:</strong> Cat eye for elegance, wispy for trend</li>
          <li><strong>Curl options:</strong> C, CC, or D depending on preference</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Round Eyes</h3>
        <p>Benefit from elongating styles:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> Cat eye style</li>
          <li><strong>Avoid:</strong> Doll eye (emphasizes roundness)</li>
          <li><strong>Curl options:</strong> C or CC curl</li>
          <li><strong>Tip:</strong> Longer lengths at outer corners</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Hooded Eyes</h3>
        <p>Need extra lift to be visible:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> Doll eye or natural with D curl</li>
          <li><strong>Curl options:</strong> D, DD, or L curl essential</li>
          <li><strong>Tip:</strong> Avoid too long lengths that get hidden</li>
          <li><strong>Focus:</strong> Maximum curl over maximum length</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Close-Set Eyes</h3>
        <p>Benefit from width-creating styles:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> Cat eye or doll eye</li>
          <li><strong>Technique:</strong> Shorter inner corner, longer outer</li>
          <li><strong>Effect:</strong> Creates illusion of wider spacing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Wide-Set Eyes</h3>
        <p>Need balance and centering:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> Doll eye or balanced natural</li>
          <li><strong>Technique:</strong> Emphasis on inner and center lashes</li>
          <li><strong>Avoid:</strong> Extreme cat eye styles</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Deep-Set Eyes</h3>
        <p>Need forward projection:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> D or DD curl for lift</li>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> Moderate lengths work best</li>
          <li><strong>Style:</strong> Natural or wispy</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Customization Options</h2>

        <h3>Mixing Curls</h3>
        <p>Combine different curls for custom effects:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>C curl on inner corners, D curl on outer</li>
          <li>Creates customized lift pattern</li>
          <li>Addresses specific eye shape needs</li>
          <li>Requires experienced Orange County lash artist</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Color Accents</h3>
        <p>Add subtle or bold color:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Brown extensions for softer look</li>
          <li>Colored tips for fun accent</li>
          <li>Ombre effects from brown to black</li>
          <li>Seasonal colors for Orange County events</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Texture Mixing</h3>
        <p>Combine classic and volume:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Hybrid sets for textured appearance</li>
          <li>Kim K wispy style very popular</li>
          <li>Balanced fullness with definition</li>
          <li>Natural yet enhanced look</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Lifestyle Considerations</h2>

        <h3>Active Orange County Lifestyle</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Best styles:</strong> Natural or light volume</li>
          <li><strong>Curl:</strong> C or CC for resilience</li>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> Moderate lengths (10-12mm)</li>
          <li><strong>Benefits:</strong> Lower maintenance, better retention</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Professional Environment</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Best styles:</strong> Natural or subtle cat eye</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Classic or light volume</li>
          <li><strong>Appropriateness:</strong> Polished without being dramatic</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Social and Evening</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Best styles:</strong> Cat eye, wispy, or dramatic</li>
          <li><strong>Volume:</strong> Medium to heavy volume</li>
          <li><strong>Events:</strong> Perfect for Orange County nightlife</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Communicating with Your Lash Artist</h2>

        <h3>What to Bring to Your Consultation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Photos of styles you love</li>
          <li>Photos of styles you want to avoid</li>
          <li>Images of your typical makeup looks</li>
          <li>Understanding of your lifestyle needs</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Key Questions to Ask</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Which style best suits my eye shape?</li>
          <li>What length is proportionate for my face?</li>
          <li>Which curl will be most visible on me?</li>
          <li>How will this style fit my lifestyle?</li>
          <li>What's the maintenance level for this style?</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Trial and Adjustment</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Your first set helps determine preferences</li>
          <li>Adjustments can be made at fill appointments</li>
          <li>Communication is key to perfect style</li>
          <li>Don't be afraid to request changes</li>
        </ul>

        <p>At Elegant Lashes by Katie, our experienced Orange County lash artists are experts at creating the perfect style for each client's unique eye shape, lifestyle, and preferences. Schedule a consultation at any of our locations to explore styles and find your perfect lash look!</p>
      </div>

